<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/322: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-24T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                            1918, 1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        11.56 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>In view recent publications in Chilean and Peruvian papers on Tacna
                                Arica dispute reported by me, I discussed question with Minister of
                                Foreign Affairs. He says that nothing at all being done by two
                                Governments concerning the question.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>